import React from "react";
import '.css/Navbar.css';
import Nav from 'react-bootstrap/Nav';

function Navbar(){
    return(
        <Nav fill className="justify-content-center navbar fixed-top stickynav" activeKey="/home">
        <Nav.Item>
          <Nav.Link href="/" className="nav-links button2">
            Skin Care
          </Nav.Link>
        </Nav.Item>         
        <Nav.Item>
          <Nav.Link href="/" className="nav-links button2">
            Body & Hand
          </Nav.Link>
        </Nav.Item>
        <Nav.Item>
          <Nav.Link eventKey="link-1" className="nav-links button2" href="/about">
            Hair
          </Nav.Link>
        </Nav.Item>
        <Nav.Item>
          <Nav.Link eventKey="link-2" className="nav-links button2" href="/comp">
            Fragnance
          </Nav.Link>
        </Nav.Item>
        <Nav.Item>
          <Nav.Link eventKey="link-2" className="nav-links button2" href="/proj">
            Home
          </Nav.Link>
        </Nav.Item>
        <Nav.Item>
          <Nav.Link eventKey="link-2" className="nav-links button2" href="/cont">
            Kits & Travel
          </Nav.Link>
        </Nav.Item>
        <Nav.Item>
          <Nav.Link eventKey="link-2" className="nav-links button2" href="/cont">
            Gifts
          </Nav.Link>
        </Nav.Item>
        <Nav.Item>
          <Nav.Link eventKey="link-2" className="nav-links button2" href="/cont">
            Read
          </Nav.Link>
        </Nav.Item>
        <Nav.Item>
          <Nav.Link eventKey="link-2" className="nav-links button2" href="/cont">
            Stores
          </Nav.Link>
        </Nav.Item>
      </Nav>
    );
}
export default Navbar;
